org.apache.taverna.provenance.item

Class ProcessProvenanceItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.taverna.provenance.item.AbstractProvenanceItem
      • org.apache.taverna.provenance.item.ProcessProvenanceItem
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProvenanceItem

    public class ProcessProvenanceItem
extends AbstractProvenanceItem
    Each time a job is received by the dispatch stack one of these will be created. It has a ProcessorProvenanceItem as its child. Its parent is a WorkflowProvenanceItem which in turn knows the unique id of the workflow the provenance is being stored for. NOTE: May be superfluous since it essentially mimics the behaviour of its child item but may be more hastle than it is worth to remove it

      • getFacadeID

        public String getFacadeID()
        As WorkflowInstanceFacades are created for a Processor the details are appended to the owning process identifier. This is in the form facadeX:dataflowY:ProcessorZ etc. This method returns the facadeX part.
